# Session Preferences and Security

- Keep responses concise and summary-first by default.
- If any requirement is uncertain, ask a short clarification question before proceeding.
- At the end of each session, ask: "Do you want me to add what we learned in this session to Cursor Rules?"

## Open-source repository safety

This website is publicly available on GitHub. Never add or expose security-sensitive information in repository files, including:

- secrets, tokens, API keys, passwords, private endpoints
- internal infrastructure details that increase attack surface
- sensitive operational or personal data

When editing content, prefer safe placeholders and environment-based configuration references instead of real credentials.
